blockingFindings[2]{id,dimension,phaseRef,description,fix}:
  B-NEW-01,feature-coverage,Phase 14,Spawn-count ceiling formula off-by-one: AC says (max=16 = 2 iterations × (1 critic + 6 reviewers + 1 integrator)) but per Q-02 the critic runs ONCE (initial create) not per iteration. Correct formula: 1 (critic) + N_iter × (6 reviewers + 1 integrator) = 1 + 2×7 = 15. Fixture assertion as written produces wrong gate.,One-line edit to Phase 14 AC + add formula comment
  B-NEW-02,phasing,M-01 Phases,M-01 milestone Phases field lists [0,1,2,3,4,5,11,13]. Phase 13 depends on 'M-01 complete'. Circular reference if executor treats M-01 membership as gate. Plan summary prose at line 1313 correctly describes Phase 13 as 'fixture verification at end of Wave 5' but the Phases field contradicts this.,Remove Phase 13 from M-01 Phases list; keep prose as authoritative

warningFindings[8]{id,dimension,phaseRef,description}:
  W-NEW-01,feature-coverage,Phase 14,C-08 machine-readable stderr line has no test helper for vitest subprocess stderr capture. Spec-vs-testability gap.
  W-NEW-02,feature-coverage,C-10 table,Halt message table claims to cover any haltReason but omits CRITIQUE_TOO_LARGE and INTEGRATOR_MODE_AMBIGUOUS rows. Table's own scope claim violated.
  W-NEW-03,feature-coverage,Phase 14,tokensUsed field referenced in Phase 14 AC but absent from ConvergenceIterationSummary schema and convergence-state.toon shape. No schema owner.
  W-NEW-04,strategy,Roadmap line 31,Cost-ceiling success metric in ROADMAP still says 'token accounting' but plan replaced with spawn-count. Documentation debt — roadmap and plan describe different measurement approaches for same metric.
  W-NEW-05,ux,C-10 / Phase 1,INTEGRATOR_NOT_FOUND and HARNESS_MISSING halt messages don't include the actual unresolved value (e.g., 'integrator X not found'). C-10 recovery strings are correct but terse.
  W-NEW-06,ux,Phase 6,CRITIQUE_TOO_LARGE truncation behavior invisible to user. No stdout warning when critic runs in degraded mode. No C-10 row.
  W-NEW-07,ux,Phase 2/3,Changelog trajectory format defined only as Phase 14 fixture assertion. No driver-layer AC requires changelog write on every converged run.
  W-NEW-08,agentic-workflow,Phase 9,Severity mapping has no dedicated unit-test AC. schema-validation.test.ts checks output shape; silent re-mapping (critical → warning) could still pass if blocking/advisory arithmetic stays balanced.

infoFindings[5]{id,dimension,description}:
  I-NEW-01,feature-coverage,C-09 progress line says document mode only. Target/criteria modes get no equivalent progress format — UX inconsistency across modes.
  I-NEW-02,strategy,M-01 milestone split-gate (W2 logical close vs W5 fixture close) is coherent but should be explicitly named in M-01 definition.
  I-NEW-03,strategy,Spawn-count formula in Phase 14 AC implicitly assumes maxIterations=2. Should be parameterized in AC comment: ceiling = maxIterations × 8 + 1 (critic).
  I-NEW-04,ux,Phase 5 scenarios numerically out-of-order in document (S-01 S-04 S-02 S-03). Cosmetic but breaks grep readability.
  I-NEW-05,agentic-workflow,Phase 4 AC references C-10 table but PLAN.md is not listed as files-in. Plan context is always in scope so unlikely to cause real defect.

